{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.3",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 3 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:1",
      "text": "After this Job opened his mouth, and cursed the day of his birth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:2",
      "text": "Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:3",
      "text": "“Let the day perish in which I was born, the night which said, ‘ There is a boy conceived.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:4",
      "text": "Let that day be darkness. Don’t let God from above seek for it, neither let the light shine on it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:5",
      "text": "Let darkness and the shadow of death claim it for their own. Let a cloud dwell on it. Let all that makes the day black terrify it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:6",
      "text": "As for that night, let thick darkness seize on it. Let it not rejoice among the days of the year. Let it not come into the number of the months.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:7",
      "text": "Behold, let that night be barren. Let no joyful voice come therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:8",
      "text": "Let them curse it who curse the day, who are ready to rouse up leviathan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:9",
      "text": "Let the stars of its twilight be dark. Let it look for light, but have none, neither let it see the eyelids of the morning,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:10",
      "text": "because it didn’t shut up the doors of my mother’s womb, nor did it hide trouble from my eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:11",
      "text": "“ Why didn’t I die from the womb? Why didn’t I give up the spirit when my mother bore me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:12",
      "text": "Why did the knees receive me? Or why the breast, that I should nurse?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:13",
      "text": "For now I should have lain down and been quiet. I should have slept, then I would have been at rest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:14",
      "text": "with kings and counselors of the earth, who built up waste places for themselves;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:15",
      "text": "or with princes who had gold, who filled their houses with silver;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:16",
      "text": "or as a hidden untimely birth I had not been, as infants who never saw light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:17",
      "text": "There the wicked cease from troubling. There the weary are at rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:18",
      "text": "There the prisoners are at ease together. They don’t hear the voice of the taskmaster.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:19",
      "text": "The small and the great are there. The servant is free from his master.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:20",
      "text": "“ Why is light given to him who is in misery, life to the bitter in soul,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:21",
      "text": "who long for death, but it doesn’t come; and dig for it more than for hidden treasures,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:22",
      "text": "who rejoice exceedingly, and are glad, when they can find the grave?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:23",
      "text": "Why is light given to a man whose way is hidden, whom God has hedged in?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:24",
      "text": "For my sighing comes before I eat. My groanings are poured out like water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:25",
      "text": "For the thing which I fear comes on me, that which I am afraid of comes to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.3.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:26",
      "text": "I am not at ease, neither am I quiet, neither do I have rest; but trouble comes.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
